"The intense sour and acidic bite crosses that line and makes it a bit harsh for me. The Smokestack Series is always one of my favorites around, and I always try to pick up the new Love Child when it comes out. Though they are never among my favorites of the style or series."
"The beer pours a very bubbly off white head that dissipates very quickly and leaves a little bit of lacing. The beer itself is a clear grapefruit red with some light brown notes. The beer smell has strong sour acidic funk notes. The funk is pretty strong and dominates most of the notes but some other notes consist of oak and light fruit with cinnamon. The beer taste is similar to the smell. The taste is very interesting. The beer starts off with the strong acidic taste but transitions to a much sweeter and sugary taste. The taste has the same cinnamon notes and fruit notes that accompany that acidic taste. The oak is not as noticeable in the taste but does have a slight presence as well as a hint of whiskey. Additionally, the fruitiness from the red wine barrel also comes out well. The mouthfeel is medium bodied but on the lighter side with a lot of carbonation and goes down smooth. Overall, one of the better and lighter wild ales that I've had."
"This is delicious. Harmony throughout the bottle and the glass, with all the elements playing off each other. Also, this beer is 9% ABV? It's dangerously well hidden."
